                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d756">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">384.11/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-10T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 10, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>44. Department’s 41, August 6, 6 p.m. The Department is today communicating again
                    with the missionary organizations in the United States urging those who have not
                    already done so to take steps looking <pb facs="0983" n="881" xml:id="pg_881"/>
                    to the immediate departure of all of their personnel from Ethiopia. In this
                    connection it is desired that you urgently renew the advice to all missionaries
                    still in Ethiopia to depart at once.</p>
                <p>Inform Department currently by telegraph of departures, plans for departure and
                    refusals to depart. Also report whether there are still any American Negroes in
                    Ethiopia and if so what plans are being made by them to leave.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
